Your joke about “what if it was all just to get laid” actually touches a real evolutionary principle. A lot of traits in animals evolve because they improve reproductive success. Communication, intelligence, humor, storytelling, and even art can function as signals of fitness in social groups. Being able to coordinate, persuade, or entertain could increase status and alliances—which historically could improve survival and mating opportunities. So while it’s not the only driver, sexual selection probably played a role alongside cooperation and survival pressures.

